Lipika IME is a many-to-many, user configurable, input method engine. Originally, designed for typing Sanskrit using Devanagari on a Mac. It can be configured to work with other Indo-European languages of similar structure.

Contriants of the current version include:
1. Support for only one class and wildcard per mapping
2. Mappings within a class definition cannot use class mapping

http://daivajnanam.blogspot.com/